{
  "texts": [
    "The motion consistency is formulated as follows,L mc = L 0 + L 1,(8)L 0 = (x pred -x gt) 2 + (y pred -y gt) 2,(9)L 1 = (∆ t x pred -∆ t x gt) 2 + (∆ t y pred -∆ t y gt) 2,(10)∆ t p = p t -p t-1,(11)where the x pred, y pred are the spatial prediction, x gt, y gt are the corresponding ground truth.",
    "The motion consistency loss endows the model smoothing tracking ability by supervised constraining the change in prediction over time.",
    "Implementation Details.",
    "The whole framework is implemented by PyTorch and the experiments were conducted on a single NVIDIA RTX2080 Ti GPU.",
    "During training, the Adam optimizer is adopted, and the learning rate is set to 5e-4 with a batch size of 8."
  ]
}